RIYADH: UAE-based hospitality platform Qstay has raised a $6.5 million seed funding round,Â in a mix of debt and equity. The company currently operates as a virtual hotel brand with 200 units as it also provides digital access to nearby pools, beaches, gyms, and spas for its guests. Founded in 2020, the company is planning to use its acquired funding to invest in technology as well as expand its footprint and product offerings.